  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct Life-Saving and Protection Assistance for Conflict-Affected Populations in Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ongoing violence and inter-community tensions continue to cause massive displacements especially in Ituri province and an increase in the number of people without access to basic services, coupled with the continued Ebola Viruses Disease outbreak in Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) and recently the COVID-19 pandemic, has placed significant pressure on the provision of and need for humanitarian assistance in eastern DRC (North Kivu, Ituri, Tanganyika Provinces). Under this project, the International Organization for Migration will directly contribute to improving the living conditions of conflict-affected internally displaced persons (IDPs) in the targeted areas; strengthening accountable service delivery for IDPs and increase affected populations&#x2019; resilience to withstand future humanitarian emergency situations.</narrative>
  </description>
